# Skills Engine

Semantic skill management via the `r2` CLI.

**Usage:** `r2 skills <command>`

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `search QUERY [-k N]` | Semantic search for skills matching a query |
| `dispatch TASK [-k N]` | Ranked skill recommendations with confidence scores |
| `info NAME` | Full details about a named skill |
| `list` | List all registered skills |
| `create NAME -d "description" [--body-file F]` | Create a new skill |
| `update NAME [-d "desc"] [--body-file F]` | Update a skill |
| `delete NAME --confirm` | Remove a skill |
| `relationships [--skill NAME]` | Show skill dependencies |
| `usage [--skill NAME] [--limit N]` | Query usage history |
| `reindex [--force]` | Re-index all skills |

- `.claude/skills/` is the source of truth. The engine adds a semantic layer on top.
- Run `r2 skills reindex` if skills were modified manually.
